      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, it's mostly about reducing unpredictable behavior. The board thinks having an AI that \"plans\" or \"reasons\" on the fly is too much of a liability. They want to move to a more deterministic, hard-coded system so there's less chance of the car doing something unexpected. It's a lot safer that way, right?",
